import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('origin').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the most popular origin?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Count: {data["count"].max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('destination').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['destination'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Count: {data['count'].max():.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most popular destination?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['count'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['count'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of trip counts?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).sum().reset_index()
    pivot = data.pivot('origin', 'destination', 'count')
    sns.heatmap(pivot, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='d')
    plt.title('What is the most common trip route?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
